  "prompt": "Do I need internet to play PS4 out the box?",
  "response": "No, you do not need an internet connection to play a PlayStation 4 (PS4) right out of the box. You can set up and use the PS4 offline to play physical game discs or downloaded games that do not require online features. Here's what you can do without an internet connection:\n\n1. **Initial Setup**: You can set up the PS4 without an internet connection, though you\u2019ll miss out on system updates that improve performance or add features.\n2. **Play Physical Games**: Game discs can be played offline without an internet connection.\n3. **Play Downloaded Games**: If you\u2019ve already downloaded and installed games, you can play them offline unless they require an online connection (e.g., multiplayer games or games with online DRM).\n\n**However, there are some things you\u2019ll need the internet for**:\n- **System Updates**: To download the latest firmware updates for the PS4.\n- **Game Updates**: To download patches or updates for your games.\n- **Online Features**: For multiplayer gaming, accessing the PlayStation Store, streaming services, or other online features.\n- **Digital Downloads**: To purchase and download games or DLC from the PlayStation Store.\n\nIf you plan to use online features, you\u2019ll need to connect your PS4 to the internet via Wi-Fi or an Ethernet cable.",
